name: Amphibia
overview: The adventures of 13-year-old, self-centered Anne Boonchuy who is magically transported to the fictitious world of Amphibia, a rural marshland full of frog-people. With the help of an excitable young frog named Sprig, Anne will become a hero and discover the first true friendship of her life.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Anne Boonchuy, a self-centered 13-year-old 7th grader, is magically transported to the fictitious world of Amphibia, a rural marshland full of frog-people, also known as Amphibians and dangerous creatures. With the help of an excitable young frog named Sprig Plantar, Anne will transform into a hero and discover the first true friendship of her life.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Anne and the Plantars are heading out on a quest to unlock the mysteries of the Calamity Box as they leave the cozy confines of Wartwood for the distant city of Newtopia. On their journey, they will visit exotic new locations, uncover hidden secrets, and experience unexpected reunions as they continue to search for a way to get Anne home.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Anne and the Plantars are transported from Amphibia to Anne's hometown of Los Angeles where the frog family will have to learn about the modern world and try to find a way home - all while hiding their identities as talking frog people.

episodes.name: Anne or Beast?
episodes.overview: Sprig tries to capture a mysterious beast to prove that he’s responsible.

episodes.name: Best Fronds
episodes.overview: Sprig takes Anne swimming in a nearby lake to help her feel less homesick.

episodes.name: Cane Crazy
episodes.overview: When Anne breaks Hop Pop's favorite cane, she and her friends set out to replace it.

episodes.name: Flood, Sweat & Tears
episodes.overview: When Anne's bedroom floods, she and Sprig must bunk together.

episodes.name: Hop Luck
episodes.overview: To win a village cooking contest, Anne leads the family on a quest to make pizza.

episodes.name: Stakeout
episodes.overview: Sprig wants Anne and Hop Pop to get along, so he tricks them into going on a stakeout.

episodes.name: The Domino Effect
episodes.overview: Anne wants to keep a caterpillar as a pet, but she'll have to keep it a secret from Hop Pop.

episodes.name: Taking Charge
episodes.overview: After one of the Plantars mysteriously runs out the charge on Anne's phone, the family embarks on a mission to try and recharge it.

episodes.name: Anne Theft Auto
episodes.overview: In an attempt to learn to drive the family snail wagon, Anne and Sprig take it for a joy ride.

episodes.name: Breakout Star
episodes.overview: Anne's pimple breakout makes her a celebrity in Wartwood.

episodes.name: Sprig Vs. Hop Pop
episodes.overview: Angry with how the Plantar farm is being run, Sprig decides to overthrow Hop Pop.

episodes.name: Girl Time
episodes.overview: Anne plans to give Polly some long-overdue girl time, whether Polly wants it or not.

episodes.name: Dating Season
episodes.overview: Anne and Hop Pop learn Sprig may like Ivy Sundew, so they attempt to set them up.

episodes.name: Anne Vs. Wild
episodes.overview: Anne pretends to like camping, which is fine until she goes dangerously overboard.

episodes.name: Contagi-Anne
episodes.overview: Anne fakes getting sick to get off work, but the rest of the family gets sick.

episodes.name: Family Shrub
episodes.overview: Sprig and Polly think their family history is boring until they uncover family secrets.

episodes.name: Lily Pad Thai
episodes.overview: Anne gets a job at Stumpy’s diner and transforms the humble frog eatery into a flashy Thai fusion restaurant.

episodes.name: Plantar’s Last Stand
episodes.overview: When rent on the Plantar’s food stand skyrockets, Anne has to show Hop Pop the key to being a great salesman.

episodes.name: Toad Tax
episodes.overview: Anne befriends toad soldiers to gain respect in Wartwood.

episodes.name: Prison Break
episodes.overview: Toad Tower finds itself under attack by a pair of horrifying herons.

episodes.name: Grubhog Day
episodes.overview: During Grubhog Day, Sprig has to decide whether to uphold his responsibilities or have fun at the carnival.

episodes.name: Hop Pop and Lock
episodes.overview: To impress Sylvia Sundew, Hop Pop asks Anne to teach him to dance.

episodes.name: Civil Wart
episodes.overview: When Anne exposes Wartwood to a teen romance film, the town splits on the movie's love triangle.

episodes.name: Hop-Popular
episodes.overview: After losing his stand, Hop Pop decides to run for mayor of Wartwood.

episodes.name: Croak and Punishment
episodes.overview: When Sprig’s rare and precious Blue Moon Shell is stolen, he and Anne investigate to find the thief.

episodes.name: Trip to the Archives
episodes.overview: To prepare for Anne’s quest, the Plantars visit the town archives and accidentally get trapped.

episodes.name: Snow Day
episodes.overview: When a winter cold snap freezes all the frogs in Wartwood, Anne must protect the townspeople.

episodes.name: Cracking Mrs. Croaker
episodes.overview: In an effort to make Mrs. Croaker like him, Sprig digs up a secret from her past.

episodes.name: A Night at the Inn
episodes.overview: The Plantars stay at a bed and breakfast for the night, but Polly discovers the caretakers aren’t what they seem.

episodes.name: Wally and Anne
episodes.overview: Everyone calls Anne crazy when she claims to have seen the mythical Moss Man.

episodes.name: Family Fishing Trip
episodes.overview: Sprig wants to spend time with Hop Pop on their family fishing trip, but Hop Pop’s friend Sylvia gets in the way.

episodes.name: Bizarre Bazaar
episodes.overview: Anne’s music box goes missing at the mysterious and exclusive Bizarre Bazaar.

episodes.name: Cursed!
episodes.overview: After Anne helps Sprig break up with Maddie, strange things start happening to them.

episodes.name: Fiddle Me This
episodes.overview: When a popular talent competition comes to Wartwood, Hop Pop goes overboard in training Sprig to win.

episodes.name: The Big Bugball Game
episodes.overview: Anne must learn the value of teamwork to win the town's annual Bugball game.

episodes.name: Combat Camp
episodes.overview: Anne, Sprig and Polly are forced to stay at a daycare center that turns out to be more than it seems.

episodes.name: Children of the Spore
episodes.overview: A scary mushroom adventure!

episodes.name: Anne of The Year
episodes.overview: Anne wins the prestigious "Frog of the Year" award and gets to plan her own party, but the frogs of Wartwood may not be ready for a human-style bash.

episodes.name: Reunion
episodes.overview: During a banquet hosted by the toads, Anne is reunited with a friend from home.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Anne Boonchuy, a self-centered 13-year-old 7th grader, is magically transported to the fictitious world of Amphibia, a rural marshland full of frog-people, also known as Amphibians and dangerous creatures. With the help of an excitable young frog named Sprig Plantar, Anne will transform into a hero and discover the first true friendship of her life.

episodes.name: Handy Anne
episodes.overview: Worried that something bad could happen while they are in Newtopia, Anne decides to disaster-proof the farm.

episodes.name: Fort in the Road
episodes.overview: Sprig longs for exotic road trip adventures, but Hop Pop’s strict road rules threaten to spoil all of his fun plans.

episodes.name: The Ballad of Hopediah Plantar
episodes.overview: Hop Pop stands up to the wrong family.

episodes.name: Anne Hunter
episodes.overview: Anne must put her self-consciousness aside in order to learn the true way of the hunter.

episodes.name: Truck Stop Polly
episodes.overview: Feeling unappreciated by her family, Polly hatches a plan to make them pay attention to her.

episodes.name: A Caravan Named Desire
episodes.overview: Hop Pop signs the family up to join a traveling theater troupe, hoping to realize his dream of being an actor.

episodes.name: Quarreler's Pass
episodes.overview: Hop Pop drops Sprig and Polly off at a trail designed to help them get along.

episodes.name: Toadcatcher
episodes.overview: Sasha and Grime must reconcile their differences to escape Newtopia’s most skilled warrior, General Yunnan.

episodes.name: Swamp and Sensibility
episodes.overview: When Anne discovers an old friend who has been living a double life, she becomes fixated on helping him be his true self.

episodes.name: Wax Museum
episodes.overview: The family visits a mysterious roadside oddities museum where every treasure comes with a price.

episodes.name: Marcy at the Gates
episodes.overview: The family must defeat an entire ant army before they enter Newtopia.

episodes.name: Scavenger Hunt
episodes.overview: Anne, Sprig and Marcy receive a mysterious message from the king of Newtopia that sends them on a puzzle-solving mission.

episodes.name: The Plantars Check In
episodes.overview: Anne finally meets with King Andrias and tries to enlist his help in getting back home.

episodes.name: Lost in Newtopia
episodes.overview: Anne and Polly vow to experience the city like locals but end up on a wild ride through the streets of Newtopia.

episodes.name: Sprig Gets Schooled
episodes.overview: Sprig is offered a spot at Newtopia University.

episodes.name: Little Frogtown
episodes.overview: Hop Pop investigates the disappearance of an old friend and the shadowy crime syndicate he suspects are behind it.

episodes.name: Hopping Mall
episodes.overview: Hop Pop takes the kids to a Newtopian shopping mall to buy souvenirs, and Anne will do anything to get the perfect gift for her mom back home.

episodes.name: The Sleepover to End All Sleepovers
episodes.overview: Anne and Marcy issue a Scare Dare Challenge that brings Sprig and Polly into forbidden areas of the castle.

episodes.name: A Day at the Aquarium
episodes.overview: Anne and the Plantars look to spend what could be their last day together at the Newtopia Aquarium.

episodes.name: The Shut-In!
episodes.overview: Anne and the Plantars protect themselves from the dangers of the annual Blue Moon by locking themselves in the house and entertaining each other with the scariest stories they can think of.

episodes.name: Night Drivers
episodes.overview: Sprig and Polly stay up all night to drive the family home.

episodes.name: Return to Wartwood
episodes.overview: The Plantars make it to Wartwood, and realize they forgot something important.

episodes.name: Ivy on the Run
episodes.overview: Fed up with her mother's strict rules, Ivy concocts a plan to run away.

episodes.name: After the Rain
episodes.overview: Anne asks Hop Pop to retrieve the music box, bringing some long-buried secrets to light.

episodes.name: The First Temple
episodes.overview: Marcy, Anne, and the Plantars travel to an ancient temple that could hold the key to getting Anne and Marcy home, but only if they can survive the temple's deadly challenges!

episodes.name: New Wartwood
episodes.overview: Intent on winning over Wartwood, Marcy makes a plan to improve the town.

episodes.name: Friend or Frobo?
episodes.overview: Desperate for fun, Polly breaks out on her own and finds an unlikely new friend in the process.

episodes.name: Toad to Redemption
episodes.overview: Mayor Toadstool is offered his dream job but realizes he doesn't want to leave Wartwood.

episodes.name: Maddie & Marcy
episodes.overview: Maddie is working on an important spell but her three baby sisters keep getting in the way.

episodes.name: The Second Temple
episodes.overview: Anne and Marcy's quest to get home takes them to an icy mountain temple, but they'll need help to find it.

episodes.name: Barrel's Warhammer
episodes.overview: Sasha and Grime go on a quest to retrieve a legendary Warhammer.

episodes.name: Bessie & MicroAngelo
episodes.overview: Bessie has her work cut out for her when she's tasked with showing MicroAngelo the ropes.

episodes.name: The Third Temple
episodes.overview: Anne and Marcy need the help of an old friend to survive a volcanic temple that holds the final key to returning home.

episodes.name: The Dinner
episodes.overview: Anne and the Plantars invite some old adversaries over for dinner to try to bury the hatchet.

episodes.name: Battle of the Bands
episodes.overview: Anne and her friends team up to enter the Wartwood Battle of the Bands contest.

episodes.name: True Colors
episodes.overview: The gang travels to Newtopia to say their goodbyes and finally send all three girls home. However, someone has other plans.

episodes.name: Hop 'Till You Drop

episodes.name: Turning Point
episodes.overview: Sasha and Grime escape from Andrias and hide out in Wartwood.

episodes.name: Thai Feud
episodes.overview: Sprig tries to get rid of a food truck that's threatening the family business.

episodes.name: Fight at the Museum

episodes.name: Sprig’s Birthday

episodes.name: Spider-Sprig

episodes.name: Olivia & Yunan
episodes.overview: Back in Amphibia, Olivia and Yunan try to rescue Marcy.

episodes.name: Hollywood Hop Pop

episodes.name: If You Give a Frog a Cookie

episodes.name: Commander Anne

episodes.name: Sprivy

episodes.overview: Sasha sends a team of her "elite" troops to take down some marauders.

episodes.name: Olm Town Road
episodes.overview: The gang look for the city of the Olms.

episodes.name: Mother of Olms
episodes.overview: Mother Olm's memory isn't what it used to be

episodes.name: Grime's Pupil
episodes.overview: Grime has to take on an apprentice, even if he is a boneless frog.

episodes.name: The Root of Evil

episodes.name: The Core & The King
episodes.overview: Introducing Darcy the latest sensation sweeping Amphibia.  Also King Andrias revisits some old memories.

episodes.name: Newts in Tights
episodes.overview: Ann finds a merry band of tight wearing newts.

episodes.name: Fight or Flight
episodes.overview: Domino II is a mommy, and she's been captured!?

episodes.name: The Three Armies
episodes.overview: Time for some team building exercises.

episodes.name: The Beginning of the End
episodes.overview: The Battle for Amphibia begins.

episodes.name: All In
episodes.overview: Hello people of Earth.  Congratulations on being conquered.

episodes.name: The Hardest Thing
episodes.overview: Is saying goodbye.
